.TH "nfp_resource_wait" 9 "nfp_resource_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_resource_wait \- Wait for resource to appear
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfp_resource_wait
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned int secs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
NFP CPP handle
.IP "name" 12
Name of the resource
.IP "secs" 12
Number of seconds to wait
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for resource to appear in the resource table, grab and release
its lock.  The wait is jiffies-based, don't expect fine granularity.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise.
